hange commit\nz i >n\nthe Bogton Stock Exchange extend- i\n\u2018ng trading privileges to include the\nfollowing iaauea:\u2014\nBraniff Airway* Inc $2.50 par j\nroad Co., voting truat certificate* for!\nno par value common Mock; Common-;\nwealth Ediaon Co.. 125 par value)\ncapital wtock General Public UtiH\ntie# Corp.. $5 par value common!\nstock; Grumman Aircraft Engineer-\nCorp.. $1 par value common atock;\nInterlake Iron Corp., no par value!\ncommon; Libby, McNeill and Libby.;\n$7 par value common. Manati Sugar\nCo.. $1 par value common: Pacific;\nCoal and Iron Co., $1 par value com\nmon. Philadelphia Electric Co., no\npar value common: Radio-Keith-Or\npheum Corp. (Delaware) $1 par value\ncommon, and Symington-Gould Corp.,\n$1 par value common Mock.\nINDUSTRIALS LEAD\nTUMBLE IN MARKET\nBrokers Find Little in News\nto Explain Down Swing\nQuotations Were at or Near\nBottom at Closing\nNew York, June 18 (AP)\u2014 \"Blue\nchip\" industrials today led a \"thin\u201d!\nstock market on one of ite sharpest\nretreats of the year and. while pres\neure was nothing exceptional, leaders\n(yielded 1 to more than 6 points.\nBrokers found little in the actual j\nnews to blame for the stumble and\nmost were inclined to attribute it toj\ndiscouraged liquidation by those who\nhad expected rhe list to push forward\nbriskly when the rails last week hit\na new average peak since 1931.\nThe failure of the upswing to de\nvelop and the inability of the car- i\ni riers to push through their highs were 1\nsaid to have been a eignal to some\ncustomers of a possible sizable tech\nnical correction. These, consequently.!\nshelved their accounts. Good earnings,\ndividends and splitups generally were;\nignored. The thought that iooked-for;\n.price-control legislation may have\nbeen discounted also was a bearish\nfactor.\nTrends began to waver after mid-,,\nday with activity expanding moderate\nly. Quotations, on the whole, were\n!at or near bottom when the final\ngong sounded. Transfers amounted to,\n1.150.000 shares compared with 1,-;\n020.000 Monday.\nThe Associated Press 60-stock.\ncomposite was off 1.1 points at 80.6. j\nwidest dip since March 13. Business,\nbroadened on the downswing with!\n1026 issues registering, the same num-\nTier as on the March tumble. Of the\ntotal. SOO declined and 110 advanced.\nBonds were irregularly lower. Cot-.\nton lost 40 cent* to $1.60 a bale. At,\n(Chicago all grain futures were un\nchanged.\nBackward curb movers were Argue\nInc.. Pharis Tire, Cities Service.\nKaiser-Frazier and Niagara Hudson\nPower. Turnoyer here was 500,000\nshares versus 440.000 yesterday.\nSALE OF RKO COMMON\nIS ARRANGED BY ATLAS\nNew York, June 18 (API Ar\nrangements for the sale of 650.000\nshares of Radio Keith Orpheum Corp,\njcommon stock by Atlas Corp, were\nannounced today.\nI \"The proposed distribution by Atlas\n(Corp, of not exceeding 650,000 shares\nlof the common stock of RKO does\nnot mean that Arias is terminating its\ni interest in RKO,\" Floyd B. Odium\npresident, stated.\nAfter rhe proposed distribution\nAtlas Corp, will still own approxi\nmately $18,000,000 aggregate market\nvalue of RKO securities. Odium\nadded.\nA registration statement has been\nfiled with the Securities and Ex\n(hange commission by Radio Keith\nOrpheum covering the sale of 670.000\n(shares of its common stock, which in\nclude th? 650.000 being sold for the\naccount of Atlas.\nIr is understood Lehman Bros, and\nGoldmann Sachs Co. will h^ad\nrhe underwriting group. Th? offering\nis expected to be made about July 9\n1946.\nKAISER-FRASER CORP.\nGETS LISTING ON CURB\nNew York. June 12 (AP)\nGovernors of the Curb exchange to\nday approved for listing, and for ad\nmission to dealings a: a later date.i\n4.000.000 outstanding shares of $1 par\ncommon stock of Kaiser-Fraser Corp.\nOf the outstanding shares. 500.000\nwere sold at the company s incept on\nio Kaiser and Graham-Paige in\nterests. 1.700.000 were sold publicly\nin September last year and I.SOO,<\u2018OO\nsol